rComments: She is one of the BEST, BEST, BEST professors at UTSC! Too bad she can't teach more courses! We want her here, not at another school! If you want a helpful, smart and a compassionate prof, than take courses she teaches. She is fair and class averages are good! LOVE HER!!!! Take her classes you won't be disappointed!

Very passionate and enthusiastic about teaching subject matter at hand. Explains concepts and ideas very clearly. She goes out of her way to make sure the students know what is expectd of them. She develops the critical thinking skills patiently that students need in University and also teaches how best to articulate answers to test questions
THE MOST AMAZING FROM THAT I"VE EVER HAD IN UTSC!!! She's AWESOME!!! She cares about her students. A very good prof. I would take every course she teaches, even if I didn't have to.

Very enthusiastic and passionate. I smiled and laughed a lot in class, but I didn't actually learn much concrete information. Very inconsistent and cryptic test questions; everyone does "OK," but it's hard to get a really good mark.

Awesome prof! Really cares about her students. Goes to show how important teaching is to her. Uses videos, hands-on tools and anecdotes to make topics clearer. She should teach more upper-year Neuro classes in the future. :D
